Explanation:

We use an unordered map to count the occurrences of each number in the array. Then, we iterate over the map to check if any number has a count that is not equal to the size of the array. If any such number is found, the function returns false, indicating that the occurrences are not unique. Otherwise, the function returns true, indicating that the occurrences are unique. The time complexity is O(n) because we iterate over the array once, and the space complexity is O(n) because we use an unordered map with n elements.

